# AMO Dashboard — Start Here

This project keeps cross-session context in two files at the repo root, shared across tools (Claude Code, Cursor, any model) so nobody has to re-derive context from scratch each session:

- **`SESSION_LOG.md`** — dated, dense summaries of what happened in past sessions: findings, decisions, in-progress work, open threads. Read it before starting substantive work. Append a new dated entry at the end of any substantive session (facts, not a transcript — keep it dense so it stays cheap to read).
- **`CLAUDE.md`** — short, durable operational facts (deploy process, LLM provider, workflow conventions). Keep both files in sync if either changes.

## Operational facts (also in CLAUDE.md — kept in sync)

- **Deploy:** production runs on a DigitalOcean droplet (`165.22.35.75`, `/opt/amo-dashboard`, **4 vCPU / 8GB RAM / 160GB disk** — resized 2026-07-21 from 1 vCPU/1GB for the full-history facility backfill; OCR workers auto-scale via `os.cpu_count()` capped at 4, and `run_facility_tick.sh` runs `--max-concurrent 4` sized for this box). The Node server (`dist/index.cjs`, port 5000) is **managed by PM2** under the app name `amo-dashboard` — PM2 auto-restarts it if killed, so never manually `kill` + relaunch (that fights PM2). Deploy sequence: `git pull` → `npm run build` → `pm2 restart amo-dashboard` (build BEFORE restart, or PM2 relaunches the old bundle). `git pull` alone does NOT update the live site. Don't kill Python backfill processes when restarting. Long-running one-off scripts (e.g. `normalize.py`) must be started with `nohup ... &` + `disown` — a dropped SSH session kills plain foreground runs (add `-u` to python for unbuffered log output). **After re-running `normalize.py`, also `pm2 restart amo-dashboard`** (or `POST /api/cache/bust` from a logged-in session) — API responses are cached in-memory for 7 days (`server/cache.ts`), so the dashboard keeps serving pre-rebuild data until the cache is cleared.
- **The user runs all droplet/production actions manually** — code changes happen in the editor (commit + push to `origin/main`), deployment is a separate manual step the user does themselves. Don't attempt to SSH or act on the droplet directly.
- **LLM provider is OpenAI** (`gpt-4.1-nano` by default) for `collector/extract_pdfs.py` and `collector/enrich_entities.py` — not Claude/Anthropic. (An earlier version of this file claimed a switch to Claude/Anthropic on 2026-06-16 — that never actually shipped; ignore any references to `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` in old notes.)
- **GitHub workflow:** every agreed-on code change should be committed and pushed to `origin/main` once confirmed.
- Local dev DB (`AMO_DB_PATH=./miami_dade_amo.db`) can lag production significantly — check actual row/date coverage before assuming it's current.
